o_description: The Open World Conference was an interdisciplinary event centered on open science and global threats, influenced by Niels Bohr's call for collaboration and trust among nations. Participants will present their work and receive feedback from peers and senior researchers, while also vying for the Bent Dalum PhD Award for promising research.
